CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 18, 1946, pg. 24, reads: "Bowling Champions - Left to right: Beatrice B... [illegible] Gwendolyn Jones, Juanita Page and Allace Graves... [ill.] women's bowling championship in the thrilling... [ill.] in the Hillvue Bowling Alleys.  The bowlers... [ill.] galore."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five women from bowling team holding duckpins bowling balls, from left: Beatrice "Bea" B., Ola Stanton, Gwendolyn Jones, Juanita Page, and Allace Graves, in Hillvue Bowling Alley
